It is disturbing that one new case was a 7-year-old girl who had been vaccinated in 2018! And she was not included among contacts of cases. Adding to the mystery is that 63 days passed without a single identifiable case. How did she become infected? And how many other similar cases have been found, i.e., one year post-vaccination? - Mod.LK]

- Tue 24 Dec 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/12/drc-ebola-cmre-update-december-24.html

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 23 Dec 2019:

News
A handwashing supplies plan implemented in Beni to fight Ebola during the Christmas and New Year festivities
- The sub-coordination of the response to the epidemic to the Ebola virus disease in Beni, through its Infection Prevention and Control Commission (PCI), has set up a plan for supplying handwashing devices for prevent all infections in public places during the Christmas and New Year festivities in Beni;
- To this end, the president of this commission, Jean-Pierre Perusi, called on Beni's parents to supervise their children well, especially with regard to putting into practice all the preventive measures that could help end the Ebola virus disease epidemic;
- Preventive measures include regular handwashing with soap and ash, getting vaccinated, and being followed for 21 days if you are in contact with an Ebola case, as well as respect for a dignified and secure burial.

Resistant to Lwemba Ebola virus disease recognizes existence of this disease
- One of the biggest resistance fighters of the Lwemba Ebola virus disease in Mandima in the province of Ituri recognized this Mon 23 Dec 2019 the existence of this disease;
- This is a pastor by the name of Paul Pauni who was also vaccinated this same Monday [23 Dec 2019] against the Ebola virus;
- Lwemba remained for several weeks without activities of the response to the Ebola virus disease epidemic following the resistance of the population to this epidemic and insecurity against the response teams.

--
