- Sat 21 Dec 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/12/drc-ebola-cmre-update-december-21.html

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 20 Dec 2019:

News

The Beni sub-coordination seeks the support of the population to put an end to the EVD in its territory.

- The coordinator of the response to the Ebola virus disease epidemic of the Beni sub-coordination, Dr. Pierre-Celeste Adikey, asked this Sat 21 Dec 2019 for press support and the population in order to definitively end this epidemic throughout the Beni area;
- He declared that epidemiological awareness and vigilance in the surrounding areas of Beni that still register positive cases remains a priority for his sub-coordination. He recalled that the follow-up of cases is progressing normally in the Beni sub-coordination.

Vaccination

- 2938 people were vaccinated with the 2nd vaccine Ad26.ZEBOV / MVA-BN-Filo (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 Karisimbi health areas in Goma;
- Beginning of vaccination around the 4 confirmed cases from 17-18 Dec 2019 in the Aloya health area in Mabalako with 4 local teams. In total, 70 people already vaccinated;
- Opening of a ring around the confirmed case on 18 Dec 2019 in the Makasi health area in Butembo in North Kivu; 19 people have been vaccinated;
- Simulation of local vaccination teams in the Biakato Mine sub-coordination in Ituri;
- Continuation of the vaccination around the case confirmed on 18 Dec 2019 in the Makasi and Maman Musayi health area in Butembo with 58 people vaccinated.

- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018 with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, 258 674 people have been vaccinated;

- Approved on 22 Oct 2019 by the Ethics Committee of the School of Public Health at the University of Kinshasa and on 23 Oct 2019 by the National Ethics Committee, the 2nd vaccine, called Ad26.ZEBOV / MVA-BN -Filo, is produced by Janssen Pharmaceuticals for Johnson & Johnson;

- This new vaccine complements the 1st, rVSV-ZEBOV, a vaccine used until then (since 8 Aug 2018) in this epidemic manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, after approval by the Ethics Committee on 20 May 2018. It was recently pre-qualified for certification.

Entry point surveillance

- Surveillance activities at the entry / control points were disrupted in some Goma control points following the security situation that prevailed throughout the morning in said city;
- Since the start of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature taken) at health checkpoints has been 129 624 795;
- To date, a total of 109 entry points (PoE) and health control points (PoC) have been established in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri in order to protect the country's major cities and avoid the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

--
