- Mon 23 Dec 2019. Beni
[7sur7, Google trans., abridged, edited]
https://7sur7.cd/index.php/2019/12/22/rdc-ebola-13-jours-sans-nouveau-cas-positif-dans-la-sous-coordination-de-beni
[Byline: Joel Kaseso]

DRC-Ebola: 13 days with no new positive cases in Beni's sub-coordination

The sub-coordination of the response from Beni (North Kivu) totaled 13 days with no new confirmed cases of Ebola virus disease. The announcement was made on Sat 21 Dec 2019 by Doctor Adikey Pierre during the communication on the evolution of the epidemic in the area.

"We haven't registered a case. Beni is on the 13th day with no new positive cases. It is Beni not as a health zone but rather as a sub-coordination. In Mutwanga, we are 105 days away. In Oicha (capital of Beni-territory, editor's note), we are on the 17th day today (Sat 21 Dec 2019)," said Adikey Pierre, coordinator of the response against Ebola in the region.

Meanwhile, in the health zone of Mabalako (Mangina), 30 km [19 mi] north of Beniville, 4 people cured of Ebola left the treatment center the same Saturday [21 Dec 2019].

--
